public abstract class GlobSet
extends java.lang.Object

A set of Globs that can be applied to an input path to figure out the set of globs that match it.

getGlobsGroupedByPrefix

public com.google.common.collect.Multimap<java.lang.String,Glob> getGlobsGroupedByPrefix()
Returns a collection of globs grouped by path prefix. A path prefix is a normalized path to a directory or file that is a (non-strict) ancestor of all paths that match the glob.
